Internet Software and Services

Company Overview of EarthLink Holdings Corp.



Snapshot People




Company Overview
As of February 27, 2017, EarthLink Holdings Corp. was acquired by Windstream Holdings, Inc. EarthLink Holdings Corp. provides managed network, security, and cloud services to business and residential customers in the United States. It operates through four segments: Enterprise/Mid-Market, Small Business, Carrier/Transport, and Consumer Services. The company offers multiprotocol label switching (MPLS), Internet protocol security for virtual private networks, and Wi-Fi and analytics; SD-WAN cloud-delivered network service; Hybrid WAN solutions; integrated voice and data solutions using IP-based connectivity over TI; and hosted voice and hosted contact center, SIP Trunking, and cable or Etherne...
As of February 27, 2017, EarthLink Holdings Corp. was acquired by Windstream Holdings, Inc. EarthLink Holdings Corp. provides managed network, security, and cloud services to business and residential customers in the United States. It operates through four segments: Enterprise/Mid-Market, Small Business, Carrier/Transport, and Consumer Services. The company offers multiprotocol label switching (MPLS), Internet protocol security for virtual private networks, and Wi-Fi and analytics; SD-WAN cloud-delivered network service; Hybrid WAN solutions; integrated voice and data solutions using IP-based connectivity over TI; and hosted voice and hosted contact center, SIP Trunking, and cable or Ethernet solutions, as well as local, long-distance, and related features over traditional copper lines. It also provides managed security services and solutions; managed cloud services; cloud connectivity and vendor selection; evaluating network, security, and compliance needs; cloud vendor selection; PCI lifecycle management, and retail business and IT consulting; and custom site surveys and quick location turn-up services. In addition, the company offers Internet, voice, and data networking services to small business customers; wholesale local access services, such as local loop access, integrated T1, Ethernet, and MPLS service with T1, Ethernet, cable, and DSL access solutions; and network transport services. Further, it provides dial-up and high-speed Internet access services; and value-added services to its Internet access services, such as security products, premium email only, home networking, email storage, as well as search and advertising services. The company offers its products and services through its call centers, search engine marketing, affinity marketing partners, resellers, and marketing alliances. The company was formerly known as EarthLink, Inc. and changed its name to EarthLink Holdings Corp. in December 2013. The company was founded in 1994 and is headquartered in Atlanta, Georgia.
Detailed Description


1170 Peachtree StreetSuite 900Atlanta, GA 30309United StatesFounded in 19941,890 Employees



